Description

The Freiburg Im Breisgau Mulhouse railway was built from 1847-1878. Reason for this the route is made up to two sections RheintalBahn Freiburg Im Breisgau-Mulheim Baden 29km length and the international section Mülhausen (Mulhouse France written in German Language) to Müllheim Baden via the Eichwald (Chalampe) Neuenburg Baden Bridge 22 km. Electrified in 1965-1981 in two different voltages 25kv 50 hz AC Mulhouse-Eichwald Railway Bridge and 15kv 16.7hz Eichwald Mulheim Baden Freiburg Im Breisgau. Reason for this occurring is that the Eichwald Neuenburg Railway Bridge over the Rhine River acts as the voltage change over point from 25kv to 15kv. Signaling systems are KVB to Eichwald (Chalampe) railway bridge where it ends, then PZB LZB Neuenburg Baden to Freiburg Im Breisgau. Combined distance with these segments are 51 km 32 mi. Making it suited for a Shorter TSW 3 Cross border route.

Rolling Stock

Notes: All rolling stock Tutorial takes place in the Training Centre since this will be made for TSW 3 as its First French German Cross Border Route. This includes the 185.0 185.1 Engine Room Start sequence and voltage changing for 185.1 185.0 & BB37000 B83500

SNCF X73900 DB BR641

Built from 1999-2004. On this route these DMU will run to Mulheim Baden or Direct to Freiburg im Breisgau

Comes in SNCF Blue & Gray Paint followed by Deutsche Bahn Red Paint

SNCF Paint Version

Below is the DB Paint with Bwget Stickers

SNCF BB37000

Built-in 2004-2006 and has working brake mode switches

Comes with I87 Fridge Wagons Habils Paper Roll Wagons Laaers 560s due to the Buggatti Factory in Mulhouse I87 refrigerator wagons Rils Pallet freight wagon LNG tanker Zagkks

Taken from French Rail Sim website http://www.activitysimulatorworld.eu/Les_wagons_transport_de_fret/Les_wagons_couverts_5.html

I87 Fridge Wagons The SNCF Equivalent to a Deutsche Bahn Ibhpps & OBB Hbbills Fridge Wagons

Taken from https://ajrailsim.pierreg.org/modeles.htm

Another SNCF Freight Wagon that will be standard for the route is a Rils Pallet freight wagon that can't run on Italian FS routes but is permitted on DB & OBB routes. Information is taken from Fret SNCF Website

Taken from

http://www.activitysimulatorworld.eu/Les_wagons_transport_de_fret/Les_wagons_couverts_6.html

Zagkks LNG Tanker wagon uses the same principle as the existing Zacns Petroleum Methanol & Jet Fuel tanker wagons. Tare weight is 45 metric tons Axle load is 22.5 metric tons taken from VTG website. Uses the Riesa-Dresden P & G brake settings

Taken from VTG Website for Zagkks tanker wagon.

For the German Side Route comes with DB BR463 Bult by Siemens from 2016 onwards Comes with Yellow and White Bwget Paint with Deutsche Bahn Logo. Alt paint scheme is a DB Red with VVO VBB stickers on the Side if one owns this route with Riesa-Dresden for the RE18 Cottbus Dresden RE15 Hoyerswerda Dresden Hbf. On this route these will do the Neuenburg Mulheim Shuttle Trips or Direct Neuenburg Freiburg Im Breisagu via Mulheim Baden

Freight Services

DB BR185.0 185.1

Older version of the Main Spessart Bahn Kassel Wurzburg 185.2 Rallion Paint DB Red Ruhr Sieg Nord version. Is equipped for France Switzerland Cross Border operations from Germany and Austria due it having PZB LZB KVB ETCS Integra Signum 1.45m Pantographs and 1.95m Pantographs. Uses in game german freight waggons and Zaggkks LNG tanker Has a working brake mode selector.

Layered Trains TSW 3 comes with DB BR401 & 403 from Kassel Wurzburg these will provide

AI traffic at Freiburg Im Breisgau

TSW 2 & 2020 as part of TSW 3 preserved collect 146.2 143 112 Regional services Freiburg to Mulheim Baden comes with own Doppelstockwagen types this includes VVO Decaled versions from Riesa-Dresden.

363 204 G6 Used for Shunting at Freiburg Im Breisgau Gbf where it interacts with BB37000 185.0 185.1 Freight services

DLC

Tutorial for these trains uses the new Training Center. These can also run on my other France to Germany route the Appenweier-Strasbourg Railway.

SNCF B85500

Built by Alstom from 2021 onwards is equipped with PZB KVB Vacma. Has the ability to run on Diesel mode in addition to Electric power 15/25kv. If a Rhein Ruhr Osten style Scenario is needed on Freiburg Breisgau Mulhouse Railway to which a Technical failure has destroyed the 15kv 16.7Hz ac & 25kv 50hz AC system you must then run the B85500 On diesel power. Has decals in French and German Languages. Is equipped with KVB VACMA PZB

Picture is by Clemens Kral on Bahnbilder.de

DB Bauriehe 650 built from 1996-2013 comes in White and Green Breisgau S-Bahn Paint DB Red OSB with Bwegt Decals. Is Equipped with Sifa PZB KVB

Service Pattern

From the SNCF Website a single Mulhause to Freiburg im Breisagu Trip takes 1hr 4 minutes this is broken down as Mulhouse to Mulheim Baden a 35 min trip then a 29 min trip Mulheim Baden to Freiburg Note SNCF Itinerary site requires the Arrival Field to be Freiburg im Breisgau as the Destination use the To then From is Mulhouse.

Pictures

The Rhine Bridge Chalampe (Eichwald) Neuenburg Baden. This marks the boundary of 25kv 50hz AC SNCF with DB 15kv 16.7hz

Mulhouse Ville End Point of the Route from Freiburg im Breisgau via Mulheim Baden and the Chalampe Rhine River Bridge

Freiburg Im Breisgau Hbf End Point of the route for Passenger services.

Freight uses Freiburg Im Breisgau Gbf where Freight trains end both BB37000 SNCF DB BR 185.0 185.1 185.2 and shunted by existing in Game Shunters 363 204 G6.

Mulheim Baden Junction for the Line to Mulhouse Ville via the Chalampe Rhine River Bridge. Rheintal Bahn goes straight to Basel

Final Thoughts

Freiburg Im Breisgau to Mulhouse Ville is a Route that should be added in TSW 3 for Various Reasons. First Reason is that it fulfils the community request of exploring parts of France and Germany that is not set in NRW RRO RSN HRR SKA Bavaria Main Spessart Bahn Munchen Augsburg. Hessen Bayern Kassel Wurzburg and France Avignon Marseille LGV. Second reason is that if made Freiburg Breisgau to Mulhouse ville offers a high speed section then a slow speed cross border section with a Voltage change involved from 15kv 16.7hz to 25kv 50hz AC France this includes new trains in the form of 185.1 185.0 BB37000 using the Chalampe Neuenburg Baden Bridge. Followed by the route offering Locomotive interactions at Freiburg im Breisgau Gbf where the existing 363 204 G6 shunt the BB37000 freight waggons then give them off to existing 185.2 185.5 182 this includes route german locomotives 185.1 185.0. Lastly Freiburg Breisgau Mulhouse Railway offers DMU cross-border operations in the form of DB Baureihe 650 641 SNCF X73900 B85500 which makes it different from electric train cross border operations. Overall these are the reasons to why Freiburg Im Breisgau Mulhouse Railway should be made for TSW3.
